Commentary: Back of a length, on leg. The ball rises sharply and Ali awkwardly tucks it to the leg side for one. The Test is underway.
Tap and run. Length ball, on off. Imran Butt taps it towards covers and takes off for a quick single.

OUT! TAKEN! There comes the first wicket and it is a dream start for the hosts! Back of a length, outside off. Ali has his feet glued to the crease and pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third slip. Jermaine Blackwood dives low to his left and takes a very good catch.
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
A touch fuller, around off. Ali blocks it out.
A solid defence off the front foot to end the over. A successful over for the hosts.
Full and way down the leg side. Butt misses the flick.
Fuller ball, on middle. Imran Butt blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Imran Butt covers his stumps and lets it go.
A full length-ball, down the leg side. Butt stays inside the crease and looks to flick it away but misses.
A good length delivery, outside off. The ball moves away a little bit. Imran Butt shoulders his arms.
On a length, on off. Butt stays back and defends it out solidly.
Fuller ball, but wide enough for Azhar Ali to leave it alone.
Great work by Joshua Da Silva. Full ball, down the leg side. Azhar Ali misses the flick. Joshua Da Silva dives to his left and collects the ball with his left hand.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Great work by Joshua Da Silva again! That is a big wicket for West Indies. Fuller ball, right in the corridor of uncertainty. Azhar Ali looks to defend but the ball moves away just enough to take the edge. Joshua Da Silva dives to his right and takes a very good catch. West Indies are on fire out there!
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: This lands on a length, outside off and nips back in. Azam leaves it alone and the ball goes over the off pole.
Full ball, on middle. Azam is solid in his defence of this one.
Back of a length, around off. Azam pushes it to covers. A wicket maiden for Roach.
Length ball, around off. Imran Butt looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Fuller ball, outside off. Imran Butt defends well inside the line of that one.
On a length, outside off. Imran Butt looks to defend but the ball goes well past the outside edge.
Beaten! Fuller ball, just outside off. Imran Butt is forced to play at it but the ball shapes away and goes past the edge.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh dear, this is a poor start for Pakistan! They have lost three batsmen in the first 4 overs! This is another very good delivery by Jayden Seales. Fuller ball, just outside off. Imran Butt is forced to play at it again but the ball nips away enough to go past the bat. Joshua Da Silva gathers the ball and the hosts start celebrating but the umpire says not out. Kraigg Brathwaite though reviews it right away and UltraEdge has a spike as the ball goes past the bat. So the faintest edge gets rid of Imran Butt.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Fuller ball, around off. Alam defends it back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off. Azam looks to cut but doesn't middle. The ball goes over point for a couple.
On a length, on leg. Tucked to the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played. Back of a length, outside off. Azam stands tall and plays it with soft hands. He guides the ball to the right of third slip and it runs to the fence.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, lands on off and nips back in. Azam looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh.
On a length, on middle. Azam clips it towards short leg.
A full-length ball, on off. Alam prods and defends it out solidly.
Alam gets off the mark. A length delivery, around off. Alam comes across and flicks it uppishly past short leg for a single.
BEATEN! This one was a ripper from Seales. On a length, just outside off. Azam stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Some movement this time. A length delivery, outside off. The ball nips away a bit off the pitch. Azam watches it carefully and shoulders his arms.
Outside off, left alone by Azam.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball gets some extra bounce off the deck. Azam leaves it without any second thought.

Shouts of 'CATCH' but the ball falls short. Back of a length, around off. Alam stays back and looks to defend it out. He is surprised by the bounce and ends up getting the outer half on it. The ball falls short of gully.
On a length, just outside off. Alam looks to poke it out but misses.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Alam has no stroke to offer this time.

CLOSE! Just over! A full-length ball, around off. Alam looks to drive but gets it from the outer half over point. Roston Chase leaps but the ball has enough height to go over him. The batters pick a couple.
Outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
A length delivery, outside off. Alam looks to push it away but misses. Good over by Roach.
Full and on off. Azam stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Slightly short and outside off. Azam stays back and cuts it through cover. The batters pick two before the fielder cuts it off.
A length delivery, around off. Azam defends it to the off side from the outer half of the bat.
On a length and on off. Azam blocks it from the outer half to the off side.
A low full toss and on off. Azam pushes it to the right of mid off. Kraigg Brathwaite dives to his right and makes a brilliant stop.

FOUR! A loosener and Azam is quick enough to latch onto it. A touch short, outside off. Azam stays back and cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary. Some positive signs for Pakistan now.
Good-length ball, outside off. Alam leaves it alone and lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and on off. Alam pushes it to cover, but cannot find the gap.
Fuller ball, around off. Alam leaves this one again.
Good length and outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Alam leaves it alone.
Full and on off. Making Alam play at it. He does so, as he blocks it out without any complications.
Good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Alam pulls his bat back in time and leaves it alone.
FOUR! A great shot. A full-length ball, on off. Azam stays back and pushes it firmly past mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race and ends up in the boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. A touch short, outside off. Azam stays back and punches it through cover. The ball races away to the boundary. Alzarri Joseph has been put on the back foot straightaway.
A length ball, outside off. Azam shoulders his arms.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Azam looks to play it to the leg side. The ball takes the outer half and goes towards cover.
OUCH! That must've hurt. Back of a length and on the bodyline. Azam hops and looks to tuck it away but misses and gets hit on his gloves.
A length ball, on the fourth stump line. Azam shoulders his arms. A good recovery by Joseph.
Fuller ball, around off. Alam looks to defend but gets it from the inner half to the leg side.
Full and on the pads. Alam works it to fine leg for one.
Fuller ball, around off. Azam is very solid in his defence of this one.
Ripper! Holder comes wide of the crease and the ball comes in with the angle. It lands around off and then shapes away just enough to go past Azam's attempted defence.
Length ball, on middle. Azam looks to work it away but gets it from the outer half towards cover.
Full and on the pads. Azam clips it past mid-wicket. The fielder chases it down and keeps it down to two.
Length ball, outside off. Alam looks to block it from the crease but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Worked to the leg side.
On a length, just outside off. Alam looks to block it from the crease again but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Good length, but wide enough for Alam to leave it with ease.
FOUR! Poor ball and punished. Full and on the pads. Alam clips it away. The man at fine leg runs to his left but has no chance to even get close to the ball.
A touch shorter, on off. Alam stays in his crease and awkwardly blocks it out.
Length ball, on off. Azam looks to defend but gets the edge back on the pads.
On a length, just outside off. Azam is beaten as the ball goes past his attempted defence.
Fuller ball, in the line of the stumps. Blocked out with ease.
Full again, but wide enough for Azam to leave this one.
Outswinger but this starts way outside off. Left alone with ease.
Fuller ball, outside off. Azam covers his stumps and leaves this alone.
Good-length ball, outside off. Alam shoulders his arms.
A length ball, on off. Alam goes back and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
A full-length ball, on off. Azam defends it to cover and takes off for a single.
Full and on off. Alam stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on the pads. Alam flicks it towards square leg.
FOUR! EDGY! A full-length ball, just outside off. Alam look to defend it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the third slip region for a boundary.
Fuller ball, around off. Azam drives it and a fumble at covers allows the single.
Full and way outside off. Left alone.
Full toss, on leg. Clipped towards mid on for one. The fielder runs to his left and throws the ball at the bowler's end but misses.
Mayers bowls a length ball, on off. Azam blocks it out.
Peach! Length ball, just outside off. Azam is forced to play at it but the ball nips away just enough to go past the edge.
On a length again, on off. Azam is hit high on the bat while looking to defend.
A full-length ball, on off. Alam defends it back to the bowler from the inner half of the bat.
A length ball, on middle. Alam moves across and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, on off. Alam moves across yet again and nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Top shot! A full-length delivery, around off. Alam uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket. The ball races away to the boundary.
A bouncer now, on middle. Alam ducks under it.
A length delivery, way outside off. The ball moves away after pitching. Alam lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Azam stays back and pokes it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the second slip, but falls short.
On off, Azam defends it out watchfully.
Good length and just outside off. Azam leaves it alone without any hesitation.
A length delivery, on off. Azam hangs back and defends it with a straight bat to the bowler.
A length ball, on the pads. Azam flicks it to the leg side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Azam lets it go to the keeper.
On a length and outside off. The ball gets an extra bounce off the pitch. Alam leaves it alone.
Nice delivery! A length ball, outside off. Moving away from the left-hander. Alam looks to defend it out but gets squared up. The ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Alam defends it to mid-wicket.
A full length ball, on off. Alam defends it out watchfully.
Fuller and on off. Alam defends it to mid off.
Brilliant from Jason Holder. Good-length ball, outside off. The ball moves away after pitching. Alam stays back and looks to cut it away but misses. The ball bounces over the outside edge.
A full-length ball, on off. Azam drives it to mid off.
Good-length delivery, on off. Azam defends it onto the pitch.
A length ball, on off. Azam stays back and pushes it to cover.
On a length and outside off. Azam leaves it alone.
A length ball, on off. Azam defends it out solidly.
On a length and on off, Azam defends it out watchfully.
Length ball, on off. Alam takes a step down the ground and blocks it out.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Alam pushes it past covers for one.
Short ball, lands outside off and stays low. Azam looks to cut but misses.
Length ball, around off. Azam looks to defend but gets the outside edge. The ball goes past the slip cordon for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out by Alam.
Length ball, outside off. Azam looks to drive but gets it from the inner half, past the stumps to deep square leg. A single is the end result.
Fuller ball, outside off. Alam looks to defend but the ball goes way past the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, on leg. Alam works it past mid-wicket for a couple.
Fuller ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on leg. Alam gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls away. They take a leg bye and that brings up 50 for Pakistan.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Alam works it towards square leg.
Fuller ball, outside off. Alam is beaten as he looks to defend this one.
Short ball, down the leg side. Left alone.
FOUR! Edged and a boundary! Length ball, outside off. Alam gets the outside edge while looking to defend. The ball goes past the diving third slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, just outside off. Alam blocks it out.
Length ball, around off. Azam chops it to the off side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Azam pushes it to the off side.
Full ball, on leg. Azam is beaten as he looks to flick it away and gets hit on the pads.
Fuller ball, on off. Azam is solid in his defence of this one.
Length ball, on leg. Azam misses his flick. They take a leg bye as the ball goes towards fine leg after hitting the pads.
On a length, on leg. Alam blocks it out.
Back of a length, on off. Azam stays in his crease and blocks it out.
FOUR! Length ball, on the pads. Azam whips it away. The man from fine leg runs to his left but the ball wins the race.
Fuller ball, on leg. Blocked out.
Full again, on off. Azam pushes it to point now.
Short of a length, outside off. Azam stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to mid on now.
Length ball, on leg. Alam works it to the leg side. No ball called as Mayers has overstepped.
On a length, down the leg side. Alam works it to fine leg for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Azam blocks it from the crease.
Mayers bowls a full one, on off. Azam works it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off. Azam blocks it solidly.
Fuller ball, on leg. Clipped to the leg side.
Length ball, on leg. Azam works it to fine leg for one. That ends the session and it is time for Lunch!
A full-length ball, outside off. Azam stays back and slashes it to point.
Some movement now! Fuller and outside off. The ball moves away a bit. Azam looks to push it away but gets beaten.
Good-length ball, outside off. Azam leaves it alone.
A length delivery, outside off. Azam lets it go to the keeper.
Another length delivery, outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Azam shoulders his arms with ease.
FOUR! CUT AWAY! Good-length ball, outside off. Azam stays back and cuts it through cover for a boundary. He really slapped that one hard.
A length delivery, outside off, moving away. Alam lets it go to the keeper.
A touch fuller and outside off. Alam has no stroke to offer.
Full and on off. Alam tucks it past mid on for a single.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Azam flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
A length delivery, outside off. Azam pushes it through covers. The batters collect two before the fielder cuts it off.
A length ball, down the leg side. Alam looks to flick it away but misses. Joshua Da Silva dives to his right to make a sharp stop.
A length ball, around middle. Alam is left with no room. He stays back and tucks it to square leg.
Good running! Full length and on off. Alam stays inside the crease and flicks it through mid-wicket. The batters pick three with ease.
A full-length ball, on off. Azam pushes it back to the bowler. Jayden Seales grabs it on a bounce.
Good length and outside off. Azam lets it go to the keeper.
Some away movement to end the over. A length delivery, outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. But it caused no harm to Azam, as he left that one with ease.
Full length and on the pads. Alam stays back and flicks it to the right of mid on. Nkrumah Bonner dives to his right and makes a brilliant stop. He keeps it down to a single.
NO BALL! A length ball, just outside off. Azam leaves it alone. Umpire signals a no ball as the bowler overstepped.
FOUR! Used the pace of the ball here. On a length and around off. Azam offers soft hands and guides it through third man. The ball races away to the boundary.
FOUR! Excellent timing and placement. A full-length ball, on middle and leg. Azam stays back and whips it through mid-wicket. The ball races away to the boundary. He moves to 45.
Outside off. Azam leaves it alone.
TWO LEG BYES! A length ball, around the hips. Azam looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards fine leg. The batters pick two leg byes.
On off, Azam works it towards mid on.
A full-length ball, on middle. Alam tucks it to square leg for a run.
Good length and outside off. Azam leaves it alone.
Nice movement! A length ball, outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Azam lets it go to the keeper.
Good length and outside off. Azam has no stroke to offer.
A length ball, on off. Azam flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A full-length ball, on off. Alam flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Azam is beaten as he looks to defend this one.
Length ball, on off. Azam clips it towards mid on. The fielder dives and stops the ball.
FOUR! Top shot to bring up the 50! Back of a length, around off. Azam arches back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary.
Length ball, on the pads. Worked down to fine leg for one.
Full ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full again, on off. Alam works it towards mid-wicket.
Looped up, full and on off. Azam pushes it through cover for a couple.
Flighted full and on off. Azam pushes it to mid off.
Full and on the pads. Azam flicks it through square leg for a single.
Looped up, outside off. Alam leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Alam drives it to cover for a single.
Full and on off. Azam defends it to short leg off the inner half.
Short ball, outside off. Cut away to point.
On a length, around off. Blocked out now.
Back of a length, around off. Alam blocks it out.
Full ball, on off. Alam looks to defend but gets it from the outer half to point.
On a length, but way outside off. Alam lets the keeper collect this one.
Full ball, on off. Alam blocks it towards mid off.
Loopy ball, on leg. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Azam pushes it to long on for one.
FOUR! Punished! Short ball, outside off. Alam rocks back and cuts it hard past point for a boundary. 100 up for Pakistan.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed past covers for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, way outside off. Azam looks to sweep it but gets hit on the pads.
Short ball, way outside off. Alam misses the cut.
Fuller ball, but way outside off. Alam leaves it with ease.
Back of a length, around off. Pushed to covers by Alam.
Full again, but wide enough for Alam to leave it with ease.
Shorter ball, on off. Alam pulls it but the man at mid-wicket dives and stops the ball.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out by Alam.
Looped up, full and on off. Azam defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Top class! Short and outside off. Azam stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary. The stand passes the 100-run mark.
On off, Azam defends it out solidly.
Full and on off. Azam blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam defends it to cover.
Floated full and on off. Azam prods and defends it out.
Full and on off. Alam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length and outside off. Alam looks to go after it but misses.
Full and on the pads. Alam flicks it through square leg for a single.
A length delivery, outside off. Azam lets it go with ease.
A length ball, on middle. Azam stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length and outside off. Azam leaves it alone for the keeper.
Floated full and on off. Alam defends it out.
Flighted full and on middle. Alam defends it out off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Alam flicks it to mid on.
Floated full and on off. Alam defends it to cover.
FOUR! Flicked away! Full and on middle. Alam stays back and flicks it past mid on. The ball races away to the boundary.
On off, pushed to cover.
A full-length ball, on off. Azam works it to mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Azam shoulders his arms.
Great stop! A full-length ball, on off. Azam pushes it to cover. The fielder there dives to his right to make a stop.
On off. Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Length and on off. Azam pushes it to point.
A length ball, on off. Alam defends it to mid off.
Slightly short and on off. Alam pulls itn hard but does not middle it. The ball meets the fielder on a bounce at mid-wicket.
FOUR! WHACKED! A short ball, on off. Alam stays back and pulls it past mid on. The ball ends up in the boundary.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Alam ducks under it.
FOUR! DISPATCHED! Short and on off. Alam stays back and pull it through mid-wicket for a boundary. This also gets up his half century. What an innings he has played for his team.
Ripper! Full and around off. Alam looks to push it away but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Full ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, on off. Azam punches it back to the bowler.
Length ball, way outside off. Left alone by Azam.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out by Azam with ease.
Full again, on off. Azam presses forward and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, wide enough for Azam to leave it.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball, on off. Alam looks to play with soft hands so the outside edge lands short of the slip cordon. It goes past third slip and runs to the fence.
Fuller ball, around off. Alam is beaten as he looks to defend.
Back of a length, around off. Alam rises with the bounce and blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Alam blocks it out.
Good-length ball, right on the off pole. Alam stays in his crease and defends this one.
Fuller ball, around off. Clipped to the leg side.
Full ball, on off. Azam blocks this off the front foot.
Yet another solid front foot defence by Azam.
Fuller ball, on off. Azam punches it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Azam defends it right under his eyes.
On a length, on off. Pushed towards point now.
Good stop. Short ball, outside off. Azam cuts it hard. The man at point dives and stops the ball.
On a length, outside off. Left alone now.
Back of a length, angling away from the off stump. Alam has no qualms in leaving this one.
Length ball, on off. Alam blocks it from the crease.
Low full toss, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball, down the leg side. Alam misses the flick. Joshua Da Silva dives to his right and gets a hand to it. The ball then rolls away and they take a bye.
Short of a length, on off. Azam pushes it towards gully.
Fuller ball, outside off. Pushed towards mid on.
Beaten! Holder bowls a length ball, just outside off. Alam goes to defend it with his hands but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone now.
Length ball, on leg. Clipped to fine leg for one.
Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Azam looks to push it away but gets the inside edge down to fine leg for one.
Length ball, on leg. Alam works it down to fine leg for one.
Good length and outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and on off. Alam stays back and defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, on off. Alam punches it to cover off the back foot.
A full-length delivery, outside off. Alam leaves it alone.
A length ball, on off. Alam flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
A length ball, around middle. Alam tucks it to mid-wicket yet again for a single.
A length delivery, outside off. Alam stays back and slaps it through cover for three runs.
A full-length ball, on off. Azam defends it to the leg side off the inner half of the bat.
A length delivery, way outside off. Azam lets it go for the keeper.
Fuller and on off. Azam drives it to mid off.
Short of a length and outside off. Azam stays back and punches it through cover.
FOUR! Classy! Overpitched and on off. Azam leans in and creams it through cover for a boundary. He moves to 64.
A length ball, on off. Alam pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone by Alam.
Full length and on off. Alam drives it down the ground but could only find the stumps at the other end.
A short ball and on middle. Alam ducks under it.
A length ball, on the pads. Alam flicks it through square leg for a couple.
Full and on off. Alam pushes it to mid off and takes off for a single.
Outside off. Alam has no interest in playing that one.
On a length and on off. Alam stays back and pushes it to cover.
A length ball, on off. Alam tucks it towards mid on off the inner half.
Good-length ball, outside off. Alam leaves it alone for the keeper.
A full-length ball, on off. Alam plays late at it. The ball takes the toe end and ends up at the slip cordon.
A length ball, on off. Alam defends it back to the bowler.
Some movement on that one! For a moment it looked like the ball kissed the outside edge. On a length, outside off. The ball nips away. Azam stays back and looks to cut it away but misses.
Another one outside off. Azam leaves it alone with ease.
Good length and outside off. Moving away. Azam lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and outside off. Azam cuts it through cover for a single.

FOUR LEG BYES! Back-of-a-length ball, on the bodyline. Alam looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball hits the body and rolls towards fine leg. Joshua Da Silva dives but cannot get there. The ball ends up in the boundary. The umpire signals a leg bye.
Full and on the pads. Alam stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1.
Short ball, outside off. Alam drags it back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off. Alam cuts it but Roston Chase at point dives and stops the ball.
FOUR! No stopping that! Short ball, way outside off. Alam cuts it past point and the ball trickles to the fence.
Full ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Pushed to covers.
On a length, wide outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Punished! Short and way outside off. Azam cuts it away. The man from deep cover runs to his right and dives but the ball wins the race. 150 up for Pakistan.

NOT OUT! Beaten! Length ball, lands on off and nips back in. Babar Azam is beaten as he looks to defend. The ball goes through the gate. Some of the fielders appeal for caught behind but Seales is not too interested. They take the review though. There is no bat on that one and UltraEdge shows that the ball flicked the thigh pads. Ball Tracker shows the impact is umpire's call and wickets are missing.
Shorter ball, outside off. Azam cuts it to deep point. The fielder from the deep fires a throw at the keeper's end but misses. Tell you what, had that hit then Babar Azam would have been gone!
Fuller ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Full ball and wide enough for Azam to leave it.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.

NOT OUT! Fuller ball, on off. Alam looks to defend but gets beaten and is hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW but turned down. Mayers has a chat with Braithwaite and the skipper takes the review with one second left on the clock. No bat on that one but it is umpire's call on hitting.
FOUR! Cracked! Short ball, way outside off. Alam cuts it past covers for a boundary.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to covers. Alam goes down after completing the quick single due to cramps.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, wide outside off. Left alone again.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Good length, on off. Alam blocks it out and goes down in pain yet again. He is really struggling with cramps here.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed towards point.
On a length, lands outside off and shapes away. Rizwan leaves this one alone.
Yorker, on leg. Mohammad Rizwan works it to mid-wicket for one.
Length ball, on off. Azam looks to defend but gets it from the outer half towards gully.
Peach of a delivery! Jayden Seales bowls a fuller ball, just outside off. Azam looks to block it out but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, around off. Mohammad Abbas pushes to to covers.

Jayden Seales makes an appeal, but the umpire is unmoved. Seales is convinced and Kraigg Brathwaite takes the reviews. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Trackers shows it is umpire's call on wickets hitting.

The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad. The players put in a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Jahmar Hamilton signals that it came from the thigh pad and the review is not taken.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally! Babar Azam departs! Fuller ball, right on the off pole. Azam looks to defend but the ball nips away enough to take the edge. It goes towards second slip and Jason Holder takes a good low catch. The umpires go up to confirm it and the soft signal is out. Replays show that Holder has his fingers under the ball. That is a big, big wicket for West Indies! They can come back strongly if they take a couple of more wickets here. Faheem Ashraf walks out to bat.
Howout: c Jason Holder b Kemar Roach

No bat on it as confirmed by Ultra edge. Ball tracker shows Umpire's call and Mohammad Rizwan has to walk back disappointed.
Howout: lbw b Jason Holder

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Two in two for Holder and West Indies are right back into this game! A short of a length ball, way outside off. Nauman Ali has a poke at it but manages a thick outside edge to the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives to his left and takes a brilliant catch. Hat-Trick ball coming up.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jason Holder

HUNDRED for Fawad Alam! What an innings this has been. His fifth century in Test Cricket. Alam pulls the shorter delivery through mid-wicket for a couple and brings up a century of high grit and determination. Gets a round of applauds from his teammates and a well deserved one. Got retired hurt on first day and now earned himself a century.

OUT! RUN OUT! Huge mix-up and Hasan Ali has to depart. Fawad Alam guides the wider delivery through backward point and calls for two straightaway. Nkrumah Bonner chases it down quickly and throws it back to the keeper. Fawad Alam decides not to take the second but Hasan Ali is already halfway down the track. Joshua Da Silva whips the bails without any fuss and that's the eight wicket down.
Howout: run out (Nkrumah Bonner / Joshua Da Silva)

Outside off, on a length. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Powell opens the face of the bat and guides it past the slip cordon for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off and Powell drives it on the up through covers for another couple.
Length, on top of off. Kept out on the off side.
Pitched up, around off and left alone.
Length again, on the pads. Powell tucks it to deep square leg for one.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to turn it on the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Full swinging delivery, on middle. Powell does well to keep it out.
This one shapes away. Pitched up, outside off and left alone by Powell.
An action replay of the previous delivery. Powell leaves it alone again.
On a good length and angled in on off. Powell defends it on the off side.

OUT! LBW! Shaheen Afridi has provided the early breakthrough. Pitches this one up on off and it just nips back in a bit, on middle. Kieran Powell looks to flick it on the leg side but gets trapped, plumb in front, and gets hit on the pads. They appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Powell dosen't reviews it and continues his long walk, back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Fullish delivery, on middle. Blocked out. End of a wicket maiden over from Shaheen Afridi.
Length ball, around off. A controlled edge down to backward point from Kraigg Brathwaite.

Huge appeal from the bowler but not given. Beautiful outswinger from Mohammad Abbas. This one was bowled on a length on middle and was shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite looked to defend it on the leg side but got hit on the pads instead. Babar Azam opts not to review it.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
This time it's the inswinger. On a length, around off and nipping in sharply. Kraigg Brathwaite doesn't pick it and gets hit high on the pads.
Full and wide, shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Fuller one, outside off. Braithwaite drives it through covers for one.
Short of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite hops back and dabs it down on the leg side.
Length ball, angled across from around off. Kraigg Brathwaite doesn't play at it.

OUT! BOWLED! Peach of a delivery from Shaheen Afridi. West Indies have been rocked early, twice. Shaheen Afridi pitches this one up on middle and allows it to swing back in. Kraigg Brathwaite is forced to play across as he tries to flick but ends up playing all around it. The ball castles into middle and leg and the skipper has to depart.
Howout: b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: This one is pushed wider. Chase watchfully leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Roston Chase shoulders arms to it.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Chase leaves it alone and it's the end of another wicket-maiden over from Shaheen Afridi.
Length ball, on the pads. Bonner looks to tuck but gets it off the pads towards short square leg.
Length ball, on top of off. Bonner inside edges it back onto the pads.
Pitched up, just outside off. Good leave from Nkrumah Bonner.
BEAUTY! Mohammad Abbas produces a gem of an outswinger. On middle and shapes away at the last moment, bamboozling the batter as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.. Babar Azam opts not to review.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Left alone by Bonner.
Spills this one down the leg side.Left alone by Bonner.
WIDE! That one shaped away a mile. Back of a length, wide outside off, ends almost towards first slip. Wide called.
Length ball, on middle. Chase blocks it out.
Length ball, around leg and shaping in. Chase looks to flick but gets rapped on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but not given. No review taken as it seemed to be pitching outside leg.
Pitched up, on off and driven straight to cover.
This one is angled across on a length outside off. Chase let's it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Pure timing from Roston Chase as he brings out a lovely straight drive. Full and swinging on middle and leg, Chase drives it back past the bowler and into the fence.
SIX! BANG! That's one way to counter-attack. Short ball, on middle and Chase just pulls it with ease over the mid-wicket fence.
Length ball, on middle. Bonner blocks it out on the leg side.
FOUR! Streaky! Length ball, outside off and shaping away. Bonner looks to leave but is late and the ball goes off the toe end of the bat and past the slip cordon into the third man fence.
Length again, on off. Bonner blocks it out.
Slightly pitched up, on middle. Bonner pushes it to short mid on.
Right on the money again from Mohammad Abbas. Nkrumah Bonner defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Bonner inside edges it to shortish square leg.
Length ball, very close to the off stump. Well left by Roston Chase.
Length ball, pushed wider this time. Chase shoulders arms to it.

Length again, this time nipping back in from off stump. Chase heaves it on the leg side from the inner half of the bat and the bat slips out of his hands and he's lucky it didn't land onto the stumps.
Fullish delivery, on the stumps. Blocked out.
Short of a length, wide outside off. Left alone by Chase.
BEATEN! Pitched up, on off and angling away. Chase looks to block but the ball just beats the outside edge. Stifled appeal from the bowler, no one else supports him.
A good length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Well played! A full ball, outside off, Bonner leans and creams his drive through covers for a boundary. The fielder tries to chase it back but to no avail.
BEATEN! This one moves away, on a length, outside off. Bonner looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle, on a length. Defended.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner opens his bat face and guides it through short third man for a couple of runs.
On a length ball, on middle. Bonner blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Chase shoulders arms to it.
Afridi hits the length hard, on off stump. Chase taps it back onto the deck.
Pitched up, wide outside off, with a hint of late movement. Chase isn't interested in offering a shot.
Very full, on off and well kept out by Roston Chase.
Full again, on middle. Chase defends it to short mid off.
Banged in short, outside leg stump. Chase ducks down and that end another maiden over from Shaheen Afridi.
Full, outside off and swinging away. Bonner leaves it alone.
FOUR! Short, but not short enough. Bonner picks it up and pulls it to the mid-wicket fence.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner let's it through to the keeper.
Pitched up, outside off and this one shapes away nicely. Nkrumah Bonner with a watchful leave.
Length again, on middle. Bonner looks to turn it onto the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball, around off. Bonner taps it to point.
Spills it down the leg side. Chase misses his flick.
Serves it full and outside off. Chase defends it on the off side.

OUT! TIMBER! Another one bites the dust! Roston Chase was squared up here! A good length ball, outside off, it lands and shapes in sharply. Chase looks to defend without any foot movement. The ball sneaks through the gate and rattles the stumps. Brilliant delivery from Faheem Ashraf.
Howout: b Faheem Ashraf

Commentary: A length ball, way outside off. Alzarri Joseph shoulders arms to it.
Another outside off delivery. Left alone.
A good length ball, around off. Kept out.
This one shapes away but lands way outside off. Left alone.
Touch fuller, outside off. Bonner lets it through.
A full ball, on middle. Bonner defends it to point.
Another outside off ball, on a length. Bonner leaves it alone.
Huge appeal for LBW turned down! A full ball, angling in, on middle and leg. Bonner looks to defend but is late to his shot. Gets rapped on the pads. Pakistan appeal but nothing is given.
A good length ball, on off. Bonner solidly blocks it.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
Angles it on middle. Joseph blocks it on the leg side.
Goes fuller now, on middle. Joseph pushes it to mid on.
Another full ball, on middle. Joseph drives it to mid on.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Joseph looks to defend but misses.
On middle, on a length, tucked on the leg side.
Very full, on middle, Bonner nudges it on the leg side.
On middle. Blocked out.
A good length ball, outside off. Kept out.
FOUR! Good shot! Touch short, outside off. Bonner hops and slaps it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full, around off, pushed to mid off. Nauman Ali starts with a no ball as signaled by the umpire.
A tossed up ball, on middle. Joseph looks to defend on the off side but gets inner half of his bat towards mid on.
A full ball, on middle. Joseph solidly blocks out.
A flatter ball, on off. Defended.
Angles a full ball, outside off. Joseph lets it through.
Another full ball, outside off. Left alone.
Very full, on middle. Blocked out. That will be STUMPS on DAY 3. West Indies trail by 263 runs.
Starts with a length ball, on off. Bonner stays back and blocks it out watchfully.
Back of a length and around off. Bonner pushes it towards point but straight to the fielder.
On a length and outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Bonner leaves it without any second thoughts.
A length ball, on the pads. Bonner stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A full-length ball, on middle and off. Bonner prods and defends it out.
Good length and outside off. Bonner shoulders his arms.
Afridi starts with a beauty! A full-length ball, outside off. The ball is moving away from the right-hander, Joseph looks to drive it away but misses.

LEG BYE! A full-length ball, on the leg stump. Joseph stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and rolls to the leg side. The batters collect a single. Afridi and company make an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Down the leg.
A yorker and on middle. Bonner stays inside the crease and digs it out to mid-wicket. They take one.
FOUR! What a shot! Full of confidence. Joseph is here to stay for long. A length ball, on off. Joseph punches it past mid off. The ball races away to the boundary.
Outside off. Left alone by Joseph.
Good length and outside off. The ball nips away a bit, Alzarri Joseph shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on off. Bonner stays back and defends it onto the pitch.

EDGED BUT SHORT! Abbas could've found an early breakthrough but that was not the case, if Mohammad Rizwan had gone for it the scene could have been different. A length ball, on off. Bonner looks to defend it out but only manage to get an outside edge. The ball flies to the left of the first slip fielder, who get low to his left but gathers the ball on a bounce.
Good length and just outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Outside off, Bonner has no stroke to offer.
On a length and outside off. Bonner lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and outside off. The ball nips in a bit. But Bonner is still happy to leave anything outside off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Don't worry says Shaheen Afridi and he strikes in his second over of the day. A length ball, around off. The ball is moving away from the right-hander. Joseph looks to defend it out but only gets an outside edge. This time though, the ball carries. Babar Azam takes a brilliant low catch at third slip. The nightwatchman has to depart. This is a bright start for the visitors and they will look to build on it.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: LEG BYE! Back of a length and around the hips. Blackwood hops and looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pad and rolls towards square leg. The batters collect a leg bye.
Short ball, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length and wide outside off. Bonner lets it go to the keeper.
On a length and outside off. The ball gets some bounce off the pitch. Bonner happily leaves it alone.
This one was closer but not close enough to make the batsman play. Good length and outside off. Bonner leaves it alone without any hesitation.
Blackwood is off the mark! Full and on the pads. Blackwood stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
JAFFA! Good length and around off. The ball moves away after pitching. Bonner looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Full and on middle. Bonner tucks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a quick single.
A length ball, on off. Blackwood stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
On a length and around off. Blackwood stays back and punches it to point but straight to the fielder.
An inswinger to end the over! A length ball, on off, nipping in. Blackwood is upto the task and defends it out quite comfortably to mid on.
Right on the money again from Afridi. Length ball, on middle. Bonner stays back and defends it out.
This one is pitched up, around off. Bonner lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length and on middle. Bonner looks to block but gets it off the outside edge towards point.
This one is pushed wider on a length and easily left alone by Bonner.
Swinging down the leg side. Bonner looks to glance it fine but misses.

Excellent end to the over from Shaheen Afridi. Bowls this one on a length around middle and the ball shapes back in. Bonner looks to tuck on the leg side but gets hit high on the pads. Stifled appeal from the bowler but not given.
Length ball, on top of middle. Blackwood defends it on the leg side.
Back of a length, on middle. Blackwood works it off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full and wide, nipping away a bit. Bonner offers no shot to it.
Outswinger, but a bit too wide to enforce a drive from Blackwood.
Length ball, outside off. Blackwood plays it with soft hands towards point.
Length ball, on off and nipping back in sharply. Bonner gets caught on the crease and the ball raps him on the pads. A bit too high and hence, no appeal.

Down the leg side. Length ball, on leg stump and swinging further down leg. Blackwood looks to flick but the ball comes off the pads and through to the keeper. Appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved.
Back of a length, on middle. Blocked out by Blackwood.
FOUR LEG BYES! Afridi strays down the leg side again and pays the price. Blackwood looked to flick but the ball came off the pads and raced away into the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Nicely timed by Jermaine Blackwood. Back of a length, and again on leg stump. Blackwood rocks back and tucks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length, around off. Blackwood watchfully defends it out.
Shorter ball, angled across and wide outside off. Blackwood shoulders arms at it.
Pitched up, around off. Well left by Bonner.
Length ball, on middle and shaping away slightly. Bonner gets behind the line to block it.
A touch fuller and on off. Bonner leans into the drive and gets it through covers for a couple of runs.
This one swung in late. Back of a length, around off and left alone by Bonner.
Another one bowled into the channel of uncertainty. Bonner keeps on leaving outside off.
Length ball, on middle. Bonner tucks it to mid-wicket.
Starts right on the money does Ashraf. On a length and on off. Blackwood blocks it out to short mid on.
Length ball, straying on the pads. Blackwood glances it towards backward square leg for a single. Appeal from the bowler but the umpire deems this as a run off the bat.
Fullish delivery, around off. Bonner stays solid in defense.
Pitched up, outside off. Bonner squeezes it through point for a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Blackwood goes back into the crease and defends it on the leg side.
Full and wide, Blackwood shoulders arms at it.
Ali starts with an outswinger. Full and just outside off. The ball nips away. Bonner lets it go to the keeper.
NO BALL! A full-length ball, around off. Bonner defends it out watchfully. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Fuller and on the fourth stump line. Bonner defends it out with ease.
Good length and outside off. Bonner shoulders his arms.
Full and on middle. Bonner stays inside the crease and defends it to mid on.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Full and outside off. Bonner stays back and punches it to the right of point. Azhar Ali moves to his left but the ball goes through and ends up in the boundary. Good shot by Bonner, he has been very patient after getting a reality check early on.
Back of a length and outside off. Bonner stays back and pushes it to point but cannot find the gap this time around.
Full and on the pads. Blackwood flicks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Blackwood stays back and defends it to cover.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Overpitched and on off. Blackwood offers full face of the bat and punches it past mid off. The ball races away to the boundary.
More runs! A length ball, on the pads. Blackwood flicks it to deep square leg. The batters pick two before the fielder cuts it off.
A full-length ball, around middle. Blackwood nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length and around off. Blackwood stays back and pushes it to cover.
Good length and outside off. Bonner lets it go to the keeper.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down! Full and on the pads. Bonner stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. Hasan Ali makes an appeal but the umpire says no. Going down leg.
NO BALL! A length ball, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone for the keeper. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.

NOT OUT! Pakistan lose a review here. Hasan Ali was sure about this one but it goes in vain. A length ball, on middle. The ball nips in a bit. Bonner stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets hit on his pads. Ali pleads for an LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Hasan Ali wants his skipper to take it upstairs and Azam does so. The Ultra Edge shows the bat is absent. The Ball Tracker confirms the ball is missing the wickets by a long way. Bonner survives and the on-field decision stands.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Back of a length ball, on off. Bonner is surprised by the bounce off the pitch. He looks to defend it out but does so with the shoulders of his blade. The ball flies over the slip cordon. The batters pick up an easy single.

EDGY! FOUR! Much-needed boundary, no matter how the runs come though. A length ball, on off. Blackwood offers his bat to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gap at the slips. The ball races away to the boundary at third man.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery by Ali to end the over. Good length and just outside off. Blackwood looks to defend it out but misses.
NO BALL! Full and on off. Bonner defends it out watchfully. The umpire signals a no ball as Ashraf oversteps.
Full length and around off. Bonner stays back and blocks it out.
Good length and outside off. Bonner lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball, outside off. Bonner has no stroke to offer.
A length ball, on off. Bonner defends it out solidly.
Yorker length delivery, on middle and leg. Bonner stays back and successfully digs it out towards mid-wicket. They take one.
FOUR! Great shot by Blackwood! Full and on the pads. Blackwood stays back and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.

FOUR LEG BYES! The runs continue to come for West Indies. Back of a length ball, on the pads. Bonner looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pads and goes towards fine leg. The ball ends up in the boundary.
A length ball, on off. Bonner defends it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Nicely played by Bonner. It was badly lined by Ali and Bonner took full advantage of it. A length ball, landing on middle and moving down leg. Bonner tickles it towards fine leg and finds the boundary.
On off, Bonner defends it out solidly.
Full-length ball, on off. Bonner prods and defends it to point. He yells a no straightaway for a single.
Good length and on off. Bonner defends it to cover.
Pitched up, on off. Blackwood puts out a stride to defend.
Back of a length, outside off. Blackwood lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length and on off. Blackwood punches it off the back foot to mid off.
Blackwood defends the length ball on middle towards short mid on.
Length again, outside off and this one swings after going past the batter. Blackwood isn't going to offer a shot to it.
Driven but without much timing. Full, outside off and Blackwood gets it off the toe end towards covers. End of a maiden over from Faheem Ashraf.
Full, on off. Bonner defends it out solidly.
Shorter delivery, on middle and leg. Bonner pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
FIFTY partnership is up! Length ball, on middle and Blackwood nudges it sweetly through mid-wicket. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length, on middle. Bonner stays solid in defense.
Shortish ball, on off. Bonner pulls it towards deep square leg for one.
NO BALL! Full and straight. Blackwood defends it back to the bowler. A no ball is called for overstepping.
Back of a length, nipping back in from around off. Blackwood hops and defends it on the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone by Bonner.
A touch fuller, on that fifth stump line. Bonner shoulders arms to it.
Length again, on top of off. Bonner defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, inviting the drive and Bonner falls for it. He misses the drive as the ball goes underneath the willow.
Pitched up, around off. Bonner defends it out with ease.

Ashraf brings out another false shot from Nkrumah Bonner. This one is pitched up, outside off and shaping in. Bonner doesn't move his feet and looks to drive but gets beaten inside the line once again.
Abbas starts with a loosener down leg. Blackwood looks to flick but misses.
FOUR! Deftly done by Blackwood. Abbas strays on the pads again and Blackwood tickles it down to the fine leg fence. 100 is up for the West Indies now.
Smart batting from Blackwood as he rotates strike immediately after the boundary. This one was on middle and Blackwood tucked it away to mid-wicket for a run.
Shortish ball, outside off. Bonner taps it towards point and picks up a single.
Length ball, on middle. Blackwood turns it to the leg side.
Back-of-a-length delivery, nips back in sharply from outside off. Blackwood hops on the back foot and manages to keep it out.
Starts with a fuller one, way outside off. Bonner lets it through to the keeper.
Full and wide again. Bonner drives it towards covers and sets off for a quick single.
CLOSE! Afridi pitches this one up, just outside off and the ball straightens a bit. Blackwood looks to block but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Length ball, shaping away from outside off. Easy leave for Blackwood.
Back of a length, on middle. Blackwood defends it to mid on.
Fullish ball, outside off. Blackwood shoulders arms to it.
A full-length ball, on the pads. Bonner flicks it to the right of short mid-wicket. Babar Azam dives to his right and makes a really good stop.
A length ball, on middle. Bonner stays inside the crease and defends it out watchfully.
Full and on the pads. Bonner tucks it short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off. Bonner squares up and defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! For all the hard work Abbas has done, it gets paid off. He finally gets himself into the wickets column. This partnership was troubling the visitors a bit, but Abbas says leave it to me. He has done the trick for Pakistan. A full-length ball, on off. Bonner looks to defend it out but misjudges it. The ball moves away off the pitch and takes the outside edge. Mohammad Rizwan takes an easy grab behind the stumps.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Mohammad Abbas

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! At one point, Abbas was finding it difficult to take wickets. But now he has got two wickets in two deliveries. Mayers has to walk back with another naught to his name. Abbas comes around the wicket for the left-hander Kyle Mayers. Abbas serves it full and around off. Mayers looks to defend it out but the ball takes the outside edge and flies towards the keeper, Mohammad Rizwan who completes the job. Abbas will be on a hat trick when he starts his next over.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Mohammad Abbas

Commentary: Back of a length and outside off. Blackwood leaves it alone for the keeper.
FOUR! Up and over! A touch short, outside off. Blackwood lifts it over the slip cordon. The ball races away to the boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Blackwood.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Blackwood prods and shoulders his arms.
CLOSE! This one could've easily dragged onto the stumps. Back of a length and around off. Blackwood looks to defend it out. The ball takes the inside edge and bounces over the stumps.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh my word, Fawad Alam just came up with a beauty to get a hold of it. His stretch was top notch. Back of a length and around off. Blackwood looks to defend it out but only manages to get an outside edge. The ball takes off and flies to the right of Fawad Alam at gully. He runs that side and puts in a late dive to grab the ball comfortably. Suddenly, the game has shifted back in the favour of the tourists.
Howout: c Fawad Alam b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: On off, Holder blocks it out solidly.
BEATEN! On a length and just outside off. Holder looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A full-length ball, on the pads. Holder looks to flick it away but misses. Holder gets hit on his pads. Abbas appeals but the umpire is not interested. Going down leg.
Good length and outside off. Holder leaves it alone.
Just over the stumps, this one. On a length, this one lands just outside off and jags in a long way. Holder shouders his arms. The ball goes past over the off stump. A risky leave this one.
On off, Holder blocks it out.
Good length and outside off. Da Silva shoulders his arms.
Full and outside off. Da Silva drives it to cover but cannot find the gap.
FOUR! BEAUTIFUL! Back of a length and around off. Da Silva stays back and pushes it through point. The ball races away to the boundary.
Outside off, Da Silva leaves it alone.
Afridi comes around the wicket now. He angles in a full-length ball, on off. Da Silva looks to defend it out but only manages to get an inside edge onto the pads.
On a length and outside off. Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on middle. The ball nips in a bit. Holder looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit high on his pads. Going down leg.
On a length and around off. Holder defends it out watchfully.
Good-length ball and outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Holder stays back and looks to have a poke at it but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A full-length ball, on off. The ball nips in a bit. Holder hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off. Holder defends it off the front foot towards cover.
A maiden for Abbas. Good length and outside off. The ball jags in after landing. Holder lets it go to the keeper.
Angled in on the pads, from around the wicket. Da Silva looks to flick but misses it onto the pads.

Overthrows! Back of a length delivery, on off. Da Silva looks to defend but inside edges it towards square leg and sets off a for a quick single. Hasan Ali has a shy at the keeper's end and the fielder backing up fumbles to allow an extra run.
Fullish ball, wide outside off. Da Silva leaves it alone.
Back of a length again, around off. Da Silva hops to defend but inside-edges it onto the pads.
Pitched up, around off. Da Silva stays solid in defense.
Fuller one, outside off. Da Silva goes for the expansive cover drive but once again inside-edges it onto the pads.
Full, on off. Holder plays it to short mid on.
Short but not short enough, on off. Holder pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! Joshua Da Silva knew it straightaway that he didn't hit it and hence, took the review without any hesitation. Length ball, outside off and shaping away. Da Silva looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge. Delayed appeal from the visitors and the umpire gives it OUT! UltraEdge shows that there is a clear gap between bat and ball and hence the decision is overturned.
Pitched up, on off. Da Silva blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! This time Joshua Da Silva has to depart! Peach of an inswinging delivery from Mohammad Abbas. This one pitches on a length around off and nips back in sharply. Da Silva looks to defend but gets caught on the crease and the ball raps him on the pads. The visitors all go up in unision and the umpire takes his time and deems it OUT! Joshua Da Silva reviews it again but the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have gone on to hit middle of middle stump. Mohammad Rizwan has once again provided the breakthrough.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Abbas

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Roach manages to keep it out.
SIX! EDGY! Holder won't mind how the runs come. Shorter one banged in on middle and leg. Holder looks to pull but top-edges it and the ball flies over the keeper's head and over the fence.
Back of a length, around off. Holder turns it on the leg side for a run.
Very full, around off. Roach jumps back to block it out.
Full and wide, angling away from the right-hander. Roach leaves it alone.
Afridi comes from around the wicket this time and serves a fuller delivery outside off. Roach makes a comfortable leave.
Roach successfully negotiates the final delivery before Lunch. Length ball, angled in on middle and Roach keeps it out. The umpires call for Lunch on Day 4.
FOUR! Delightful! A full-length ball, on off. Holder gets behind the line and drives it past mid on. The ball races away to the boundary. He has come out with some positive attitude.
Full and on off. Holder stays back and defends it out solidly.

FOUR! That is very impressive. Full length and just outside off. Holder hangs back and creams it through cover. The ball races away to the boundary. The second one of the over. Holder holds his pose as well, for the photographers.
A length ball, on off. Holder defends it out solidly.
BEATEN! Back of a length, in the channel of uncertainty. Holder looks to have a poke at it but gets beaten.
Good length and outside off. Holder shoulders his arms. A good start to the session for West Indies.
Back of a length and around off. Roach though about ducking but he misjudges it completely. The ball nips in a bit and Roach gets hit near his armpits.
A touch short, on off. Roach stays back and defends it out awkwardly off the gloves.
Afridi fires in a short ball, just outside off. Roach leaves it alone for the keeper.

NOT OUT! Another review goes in vain for Pakistan. Back-of-a-length ball, just outside off. Roach looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge. There was some noise insists Shaheen Afridi and Azam supports him by taking the review. The UlraEdge shows that the bat is absent. Kemar Roach survives.
Full length and just outside off. Roach looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A sharp bouncer on middle. Roach ducks under it.
SIX! All the way! You cannot ask for a more clean strike. A length ball, on off. Holder stands tall and powers it over the long on fence for a biggie.
On off, pushed to cover.
A length ball, on the bodyline. Holder stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket. They take one.
On a length, around off. Roach defends it to cover.
A full-length ball, on off. Roach defends it out solidly.
Good length and outside off. Roach comes across and leaves it alone.
A length ball, around off. The ball nips in a bit. Holder lets it go to the keeper.
Angles in a length ball, on off. Holder defends it back to the bowler.
On a length and around off. Holder lifts it over the bowler's head. The ball goes towards long off. The batters take two.
A length ball, on off. Holder whips it through square leg for a single.
Angles in a length ball, onto the pads. Roach tucks it to deep square leg for a single. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! It is a 5-fer for Shaheen Afridi. What a game he is having. He has gotten Holder to depart, who was also the last hope for West Indies. A full-length ball, outside off. The ball nips away a bit. Holder stays back and looks to play the cover drive but mistimes it completely. The ball takes the outside edge and Mohammad Rizwan does the rest behind the wickets.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Full and on the pads. Seales flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Roach plays it to covers.
A quick bumper, on middle. Roach ducks under it.
Length ball, on middle. Roach defends it on the leg side.
Full, on off and driven straight to mid off.
Full again, on off. Roach looks to cover drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards deep mid-wicket. They take one.
Ali comes from the around the wicket to the left-hander and serves this one full outside off. Seales shoulders arms.
SIX! WOW! Banged in short, around middle. Roach stays back and dispatches it over the square leg fence.
Length ball, straying down leg. Roach looks to pull hard but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! West Indies have been bundled out for 150 runs! Babar Azam takes a stunning one-handed catch to dismiss Kemar Roach. Afridi pitches this one up, on middle. Roach goes for the big heave over mid-wicket but doesn't manage to clear Babar Azam, who jumps up and takes a beauty. Shaheen Afridi gets his sixth wicket and that's a career-best for him in an innings of a Test match.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Starts with a swinging delivery, down the leg side. Butt looks to flick but misses and Joshua Da Silva makes a good diving stop to his left.

Big inswinger from Roach. Pitched this one up on middle and the ball comes back in sharply. Butt gets rapped on the pads and Roach lets out a big appeal. The umpire shakes his head and Kraigg Brathwaite decides not to review.
Full, on off. Butt punches it to mid off.
On a length, around off and nipping back in. Butt defends it on the off side.

FOUR BYES! Roach strays down the leg side again and pays the price. This one swings way down the leg side and the keeper can't get to it. The ball races towards the fine leg fence. Pakistan are off the mark in their second innings.
Pitched up, on off. Butt blocks it out.

FOUR! Streaky boundary from Abid Ali to get underway. Seales bowls a peach of a delivery, on off and this one straightens. Ali looks to defend but the ball catches the outside edge and goes through the slip cordon for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Abid Ali. A bit too straight from Seales on the leg stump. Abid Ali flicks it really fine for a boundary.
Full, on off and shaping away. Ali drives it straight to mid off.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over and the runs are flowing for Pakistan. Shortish delivery, outside off. Ali rocks back and guides it through backward point and into the fence.
Back of a length, around off. Ali hops looking to play it on the off side but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
WIDE! Quick bumper, on off. Abid Ali ducks underneath. The square leg umpire calls it a wide.
Pitched up, around off and beats the outside edge of Ali who was looking to block.
Full, on the pads. Butt flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
FOUR LEG BYES! Roach hasn't got a hold of his line yet as he strays onto the pads again. Butt looks to flick but the ball comes off the pads and races into the fine leg fence.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Butt tucks it on the leg side.
Length ball, straying down leg. Butt looks to flick but misses. There's a shout from the fielders but Roach isn't interested and neither is the umpire.

FOUR! LUCKY! That one could have easily chopped back onto the stumps. Pitched up, on off and Butt looks to drive. He gets the inside edge and the ball goes past leg stump and into the fine leg boundary.
Length, on off and blocked out by Butt.
Length ball, around off. Ali defends it on the off side.
FOUR! Abid Ali has absolutely creamed this one through cover-point. Length ball, outside off and shaping away. Ali hits it with the swing and picks up another boundary.
Good comeback from Jayden Seales. Pitches this one up, on that fifth stump line and the ball shapes away. Ali looks to push at it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
A touch shorter, outside off. Ali hops back and cuts it to deep point for a run.
Fullish delivery, on middle. Butt plays it with soft hands towards cover.

Back of a length, outside off. Butt is late in pulling out of the shot and the ball comes off the toe end of the bat towards gully, where Shai Hope, the substitute fielder makes a diving stop to his left.
Length ball, on top of off. Ali works it to deep mid-wicket for one. A no ball is called for overstepping.
Length again, on middle. Butt tucks it behind square for a run.
Slightly fuller, outside off. Ali taps it on the off side.
On a good length, outside off and this one bounces a bit extra. Ali looks to play it on the off side but misses.
LEG BYE! Fullish delivery, angled in on middle and leg. Ali looks to flick but the ball comes off the pads and rolls towards fine leg. They get a leg bye.
Pitched up, around off and Butt gets beaten all ends up as he looks to drive.
Length ball, on the pads. Butt works it behind square on the leg side and calls for two straightaway. He puts in the dive to make sure that he gets back in safely.
A full-length ball, on the pads. Ali removes his front leg and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Good running.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short ball, outside off. Butt stays back and upper cuts it over point. The ball ends up in the boundary. The openers are batting so freely.
FOUR! This is the sixth boundary off Jayden Seales. Full and on the pads. Butt flicks it through square leg. The ball races away to the boundary. The lead moves to 199.
Full and outside off. Butt pushes it to cover. Nkrumah Bonner dives to his right to make an excellent stop.
Full and on the pads. Butt tucks it to mid-wicket for a single. The lead moves to 200.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! A length ball, around off. Ali looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the left of gully. The fielder there misfields and the ball ends up in the boundary at third man. Also, the 50 run partnership is up for the batters.

NOT OUT! A desperate review goes in vain for West Indies. An appeal for LBW but turned down. Holder serves a length ball, on leg. Butt stays inside the crease and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Holder makes an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. He convinces his skipper to take it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows the ball is missing the wicket. Imran Butt lives on.
A length ball, outside off. This one nips in a bit. Butt comes forwards and looks to play it on the leg side but misses and gets hit on his pads. The ball rolls towards the slip cordon.
A length ball, on off. Butt pushes it to cover for a single.
Full and on the pads. Ali tucks it through mid-wicket for another single.
Full and on off. Butt stays inside the crease and defends it out solidly.
Angles in a length  ball, onto the pads. Butt stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for another single.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length and outside off. Butt looks to go after it but misses.
FOUR! CUT AWAY! Short and wide outside off. Butt stays back and cuts it through point. The ball goes through the gap and ends up in the fence.
A length ball, on off. Butt pushes it to mid off for a single. He did not middle that one.
A full-length ball, on off. Ali stays back and works it through cover off the outer half. The initial call was for two runs but the batters only get one.
SWING AND A MISS! A length ball, outside off. Butt looks to chase it but misses. Joshua Da Silva could not collect the ball, as it took a bounce just in front of him.
A length ball, on the pads. Butt works it to the right of mid on for a single.
A length ball, sliding down the leg side. Butt leaves it alone. Joshua Da Silva moves to his left and takes it comfortably.
IN THE AIR..SAFE! A short ball, on off. Butt stays back and pulls it uppishly towards deep square leg. The ball lands safely in a vacant area. The batters take two.
A length ball, on the pads. Butt tucks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR Tickled away! Full and on the pads. Ali removes his front leg and glances it towards fine leg. The ball ends up in the boundary.
On off, kept out by Ali.
BEATEN! Good length and outside off. Ali hangs back and looks to push it out but misses.
A length ball, on off. Butt pulls it towards mid-wicket off the inner half. They take one.
A length  ball, on off. Ali works it to the off side off the outer half.

OUT! CAUGHT! Alzarri Joseph gives the breakthrough the West Indies were looking for. On a length and around off. Ali stays back and guides it towards gully but cannot find the gap. He gifts it to the fielder and the substitute fielder, Shai Hope makes no mistake at gully and gulps down a low catch. Pakistan lead by 222 runs.
Howout: c sub Shai Hope b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Ali pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! Good length and outside off. Ali stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Full length and on off. Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, on middle. Butt drives it past mid on for a run.
Pitched up, outside off and Azhar Ali leaves it alone.
LEG BYE! Length ball, on middle and leg. Ali looks to work it on the leg side but the ball hits the pads and goes towards square leg. They take a leg bye.
Length ball, sliding on the pads. Butt works it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Back of a length, on middle. Ali defends it towards mid on.
Length again, on off and this one stays a bit low. Azhar Ali manages to keep it out but he is yet to get off the mark in this Test match.
FOUR! That one sounded so sweet. Imran Butt shimmies down the track and absolutely creams the length delivery through covers for a boundary.
Fuller one, outside off. Butt looks to drive but misses.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Butt pulls it to deep backward square leg for a run.

Azhar Ali is finally off the mark in this match. Short ball, on middle. Ali pulls it in front of square on the leg side and races back for the third. There is a direct hit at the keeper's end but the batter is well in.
On a good length and on off. Butt blocks it out.
Back of a length, on off. Butt defends it off the back foot.
Mayers sees Ali charging down the track and fires it in full and wide. Nothing Ali can do about that one.
FOUR! Short and wide, Ali cuts it with ease to the vacant backward point fence.
FOUR! Pure timing from Azhar Ali. A touch fuller, outside off and Ali drives it on the up through covers for another boundary.
Full, outside off. Ali squeezes it out to point for a quick single.
Fullish delivery, around off. Butt taps it to short cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nkrumah Bonner has taken a blinder! Full and very wide, Imran Butt chases it away from his body and pays the ultimate price. Butt slashes hard at it but does not get enough elevation on it. Nkrumah Bonner, at point, takes a step to his right and jumps up to pluck the ball out of thin air. West Indies have the second breakthrough but Pakistan's lead is 242.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: Floated, on the pads. Ali defends it on the leg side.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Ali uses his feet and works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up again, on middle. Babar Azam uses his feet and hits it to wide long on. He gets off the mark with a single.
Flighted on middle. Ali flicks it on the leg side.
Floated delivery, very slow on the pads. Ali tucks it to square leg.
BYE! Tossed up, outside leg stump and this one turns a bit, beating the batsman. Joshua Da Silva does well to get a foot on it as the ball rolls towards short fine leg. The batters get a bye.
Length ball, outside off. Ali plays it through covers for a run.
Full and wide, Azam drives it to sweeper cover for one.
Full and very wide. Ali chases it and manages to toe end it through covers. They take one.
Length ball, around off. Babar Azam hits it through the infield on the off side and picks up a run.
This one is full and wide again. Ali hits it past cover into the deep for one.
Full and wide. Azam looks to use his feet but manages to bunt it onto the deck.
Flighted, down the leg side. Ali leaves it alone.
Floated, full and down leg. Ali looks to play the reverse sweep but misses.
Flighted, on the pads. Ali sweeps it to the left of the man at leg slip.
Looped up, down leg again. Ali sweeps and gets a thin edge on it. The ball rolls towards third man off the keeper. The take one.
Darted on the pads. Azam pushes it out and takes off for a single. 100 is up for Pakistan. The lead moves to 252.
On middle, Ali plays the paddle sweep but does not connect well.
Full and wide outside off. Azam comes across and leaves it alone.
A full-length delivery, outside off. Azam guides it to the right of third man for a single.
Full and outside off. The ball lands and nips away. Ali leaves it alone. He was looking for a wide but the umpire thinks otherwise.
A length ball, on off. The ball stays low. Ali steers it towards point and rotates the strike.
A length ball, on off. Azam pushes it to mid off.
WIDE! Full and wide outside off. Azam leaves it alone. Umpire calls it as a wide.
Full-length ball, on off. Azam drives it hard towards cover but straight to the fielder.
Flighted on the pads. Ali tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Finally Ali gets the connection he was looking for since the last over. Flighted full and down leg. Ali reverse sweeps it through cover. The ball ends up in the boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kraigg Brathwaite picks up a wicket. What a comeback by him, after getting hit for a boundary. Looped up, full and on leg. Ali gets low and looks to sweep it away. The ball takes the top edge and flies towards the man at short fine leg. Jermaine Blackwood settles under it and takes an easy catch. Pakistan lead by 259 runs and THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4.
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: WIDE! Flighted down the leg side. Ali leaves it alone. Wide called.
Floated, down the leg side. Ali lets it go. This time the umpire does not call it a wide.
WIDE! Looped up, full and down leg. Ali leaves it alone. Wide called.

NOT OUT! The ball was pitching outside leg and Ali gets a lifeline. Flighted, on leg. Ali stays inside the crease and looks to flick it but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite and company make an appeal. The umpire raises his finger after quite some thinking. Hasan Ali takes a review straightaway. The UltraEdge shows the bat is absent. The Ball Tracker shows the ball is pitching outside leg. The umpire has to reverse his decision. Hasan Ali survives.
SIX! ALL THE WAY! The only reason why Ali has come out. Looped up, down leg. Ali gets behind the line of the delivery and heaves it over the square leg fence for a maximum.
A length ball, on off, pushed to cover for a single.
WIDE! Full and wide outside off. The ball nips away a bit. Ali leaves it alone. Wide called.
IN THE AIR...SAFE! A full-length ball, on off. Ali throws his bat at it. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards third man. The ball meets the man there on a bounce. They take one.
A length ball, on off. Azam lifts it towards long on for a single.

DROPPED! A length ball, on off. Ali hits it high in the air toward sweeper cover. Shai Hope comes running in but could not grab the ball cleanly in the end. The batters get two and a wild throw from Hope leads to an extra run. They get three runs in total.
On off, pushed to cover for a single.
SIX! BANG! Full and outside off. Ali comes across and smokes it over the long on fence for a maximum. The lead moves to 281.

NOT OUT! Joshua Da Silva wanted Kraigg Brathwaite to bowl outside off and he does so. Flatter and outside off. Azam swings hard at it but misses. Joshua Da Silva collects the ball and shatters the stumps in no time. He thinks Azam has his back leg in the air and makes an appeal for stumping. The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays roll in and show Azam had his back leg grounded behind the crease.
SIX! It is out of here. Loopy ball, full and on off. Azam skips down the track and heaves it over the long on fence for a maximum.

NOT OUT! WIDE! Loopy ball, down leg. Azam looks to flick but misses. The ball hits Joshua Da Silva and rolls to the off side. Azam is unaware where the ball is and he ventures out of the crease. Joshua Da Silva collects the ball and is quick to uproot the off stump. Azam though reacted quickly and gets his bat inside the crease. The umpire though takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays roll in and show Azam was safe.
FOUR! TICKLED AWAY! Darted on the pads. Azam glances it towards fine leg and finds the boundary.
Short and on off. Azam pulls it to square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, down leg. Ali looks to flick it away but misses.
On leg, Ali flicks it to short fine leg.
Full and wide, outside off. Azam leaves it alone.
Low full toss, around off. Azam drives it to cover.
Full, outside off. Azam creams it straight to the cover fielder.
Full and wide again from Mayers. Babar Azam manages to reach it and squeeze it out to deep point for a run.
